Interface ProtectionGroups

    public interface ProtectionGroups
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ProtectionGroupsTypes
    The ProtectionGroups interface provides methods for managing protection groups created for a cluster.

        java.lang.String pause_Task(java.lang.String cluster,
                            java.lang.String pg)
        Pause the specified proteciton group. This action pauses all periodic snapshot operations and deletion of expired snapshots. Any ongoing snapshot creation or deletion operations will not be paused.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation is a task identifier which will be returned by this method.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        identifier for the task created by this API invocation
        Throws:
        Error - If there is unknown internal error.
        AlreadyInDesiredState - If the protection group is already paused.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - If there is another operation in progress.
